com.moback.android

Class MoBackObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.moback.android.MoBackObject

  • public class MoBackObject
extends Object
    This class is to be extended to contain any extra data types that are part of your corresponding MoBack table.
    The table name used is specified by either the name of the class that extends MoBackObject, or by using the MoBackTableName annotation.

        public static void fetchAll(Class classToCreate,

            FetchMultipleCompletionBlock completion)
        This makes an API call to get all instances of this object and return them.
        Parameters:
        classToCreate - The class that we will create objects of.
        query - The Query object to send with the request to select which objects will be returned. If it's null, this just selects all items.
        completion - The callback to use when the API call is finished. The objects fetched are returned here.

      • fetchObject

        public static void fetchObject(Class classToGet,
               String id,
               FetchSingleCompletionBlock completion)
        Refresh the data in this object from what's stored in MoBack. The Object containing the new data is returned as the first [0] element of the callback's array.

        The callback returns an error if this object wasn't created/retrieved from MoBack.

        Parameters:
        completion - The callback to use when this object gets updated. Exception thrown if null.
